June 15, 2003 - Senate bill S724 is being held in committee by Senators Kohl and Hatch until weight limits are imposed on it. Senator Kohl, one of the authors of the Safe Explosive Act (SEA), has been against S724 from the beginning. Since Kohl is an author of the SEA, all other Democrats on the committee, except Senator Durbin, have decided to follow Senator Kohl's lead on the matter. Senator Hatch is uncomfortable with permitting American citizens to have unrestricted access to ammonium perchlorate composite rocket propellant. The weight limits being discussed within the committee are extremely low. As a result ARSA has started a new letter and phone campaign in the hopes of turning this situation around.<br>
