June 15, 2003 - Senator Herb Kohl representing the state of Wisconsin has had ATFE agents on his staff since 2001. Senator Kohl is one of the coauthors of the Safe Explosives Act (SEA) which was strongly endorsed by the ATFE and was added as an amendment to the Homeland Security Act. The SEA has resulted in widespread disruptions in the transportation of explosives in the United States. <br>
<br>
Senator Kohl's SEA has also created a major crisis for hobby rocketry and &quot;hands on&quot; aerospace education programs within the United States. Senator Mike Enzi from Wyoming has introduced Senate bill S724 to fix these problems. The bill has 12 cosponsors. Currently, the bill is trapped in the Senate Judiciary Committee where Senator Kohl is a member. Other Democrats on the committee, except Senator Durbin, are deferring to Senator Kohl on the bill. The ATFE is strongly opposed to S724 as is Senator <br>
