<br>
if passed as ammended, S.724 make us far from OK. What is a &quot;recreational model rocket&quot;? One that is 1 lb? 3.3 lb? The exemption only applies to them. What is a &quot;model rocket motor&quot;? &lt; 0.9 lbs, but at any impulse? What about L2 or L3 flyers who cannot get storage, and so cannot get a LEUP? are they OK? what about dealers that can't meet the SEA storage requirements &gt; 25 lbs, are they OK?<br>
<br>
the 'averaging of the two' bills will result in a less restrictive final bill, if we can get S.724 as ammended less restrictive. The floor is now the place to take that on. Or even better, restore S.724 as introduced. It is difficult, but it can be done on the floor.<br>
<br>
sacrificing AM/EX and everything it supports; like innovation, and the human resource pipeline that feeds commercial aerospace; in order to preserve a TRA/NAR HPR agenda, is that OK?<br>
<br>
what about our government? should it be allowed to make laws based on ignorance and irrational fears? is that OK?<br>
<br>
I don't think ANY of it is OK.  I agree with John Wickman, the ammended bill is &quot;unacceptable&quot;<br>
