<br>
nowhere in this Hatch/Kohl S.724 does it say that APCP motors &lt; 62.5g are exempted from consideration for the purpose of total weight calculation, it refers only to APCP 'propellant' weight.  <br>
<br>
all APCP regardless of weight contributes to the 25 lb limit before the LEUP requirement kicks in.  This is further supported by the references to &quot;propellant for purposes of powering recreational model rockets&quot; and &quot;model rocket motors&quot;, without weight distinction<br>
<br>
does anyone believe that the ATFE can exempt 62.5g for weight consideration in REGS when LAW now sets specific weight thresholds for APCP possession and storage?<br>
<br>
furthermore, the LEUP requires evidence of storage regardless of whether you intend to exceed 50 lbs of storage or not, as the LEUP *enables* you to acquire more than 50 lbs, where a Type 4 magazine is required.  So over 25 lbs means LEUP and evidence of storage capability<br>
<br>
even &gt; 25 lbs of F &amp; G APCP motors<br>
<br>
this is death to even MPR motor resellers who for whatever reason cannot obtain storage.<br>
<br>
- iz<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iz55>iz55</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/22/03 12:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=113>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  correction of previous ERRATA</span><hr size=1> in Hatch/Kohl substitute S.724 18USC40, Sec 845(a)(7) says that 2 lbs BP, matches, ignitors and APCP motors not greater than 0.9 lbs are exempt from Sec 842(j)<br>
<br>
so as 0.9 lbs and under do not contribute to 25 lbs, an unlimited number of 0.9 lb motors may be possessed exempt from permitting and regulated storage<br>
<br>
you really have to see a marked-up 18USC40 to get that<br>
<br>
this being the case, a non-permittee never reaches a 25 lb threshold, as it is unlawful for him to acquire motors &gt; 0.9 lbs.   <br>
<br>
ergo the 25 lb limit applies to only permitees' motors &gt; 0.9 lbs <br>
<br>
now MPR and &quot;low end&quot; HPR and their dealers are in from the cold<br>
the balance of HPR, and all AM/EX (where APCP is used) and their dealers are still in in the frigid waters of the north atlantic with no lights in sight<br>
<br>
&quot;brrrrrr&quot; !<br>
<br>
we can do much better than this<br>
<br>
