in addition, I have concerns about the following ambiquities:<br>
<br>
Sec. 845(a)(7) says<br>
<br>
&quot; ... model rocket motors containing no more than .9 pounds of ammonium perchlorate composite propellant ... &quot;<br>
<br>
note that this doesn't say &quot;grains&quot;, nor does it say &quot;assembled motors&quot;, it just says &quot;motors&quot;.   So, does this exemption not apply to reloads? Does it only apply to SU motors?  That is NPRM 968 codified in law!<br>
<br>
the answer may depend on the definition of &quot;model rocket motor&quot; (which I would not feel comfortable leaving to the ATF)<br>
